><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3612084\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3612084\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bei1665702859812.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bei1665702859812.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bei1665702859812.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bei1665702859812\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Configuring the Uniface Debugger\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can configure the Uniface Debugger by setting breakpoints and watches, and selecting preferences and settings from the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">View</span> menu. The Uniface Debugger settings, watches, and breakpoints make up its state, which can be saved to the configuration file for repeated use.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"bei1665702859812__li_d9167e1_d9168e1_d9169e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"bei1665702859812__p_d18866e1_d18867e1_d18868e1\">Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">View &gt; Settings</span></span>, click the desired tab, and select the various diagnostic settings you\n               want. Then click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Apply</span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1__entry__1\">Tab </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1__entry__2\">Purpose </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">I/O Print</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1__entry__2\">Choose the level of I/O messages that are\n                              displayed in the message frame or transcript window. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Tracing</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1__entry__2\">Choose the level or type of\n                              ProcScript-related tracing to be displayed in the message frame or\n                              transcript window. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Triggers</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1__entry__2\">Choose the triggers you want to be\n                              enabled or disabled for debugging, or those that you want to be set as\n                              breakpoints. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Errors</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1__entry__2\">Set a specific ProcScript error or\n                              exception value (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span>) as a breakpoint. See\n                                 <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lbe1677053515050.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lbe1677053515050.html\" title=\"The following procedure allows developers to enable or disable Uniface debugger breakpoints based on the defined errors or exceptions break-on conditions on the Settings &gt; Error configuration tab.\">Configuring the Debugger Error and Exception behavior</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Message Frame</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bei1665702859812__table_d2087e1_d2088e1_d2089e1__entry__2\">Specify whether the\n                                 <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">clrmess</span> ProcScript instruction is enabled or\n                              disabled (the default in the Debugger), and display location of\n                              application messages. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\">For information on specific settings, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">F1</span> to display\n                  the online help.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"bei1665702859812__note_w2134ab1b5b1b1b3b3_w2135ab1b5b1b1b3_w2136ab1b5b1b1_w2137ab1b5b1_w2138ab1b5_w2139ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Triggers</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Errors</span>\n                  tabs enable you to set general breakpoints. You can also set specific breakpoints\n                  in the Debugger main window. See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qrs1665702859881.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qrs1665702859881.html\" title=\"Set breakpoints on ProcScript instructions, triggers, errors, or conditions.\">Working with breakpoints</a>.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"bei1665702859812__li_d9170e1_d9171e1_d9172e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"bei1665702859812__p_d18869e1_d18870e1_d18871e1\">Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">View &gt;Preferences</span></span>, and select the desired Debugger startup, close, and display\n               preferences. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">By default, <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">On close: save state &amp; preferences</span> is\n                  selected. This ensures that the current state is automatically saved when the\n                  Debugger is closed. You can change this, and any other preferences as desired.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"bei1665702859812__li_d9173e1_d9174e1_d9175e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Optionally, save the current state as a named state.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<ol class=\"ol\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bei1665702859812__li_d9176e1_d9177e1_d9178e1\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Add</span> and provide a name and description for the state.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bei1665702859812__li_d9179e1_d9180e1_d9181e1\">Click the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Save</span> to insert a new section with this name and description, containing the current active state, in the configuration file.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bei1665702859812__li_d9182e1_d9183e1_d9184e1\">If you want to update the default state using the current active state, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Update Default</span>.\n <div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"bei1665702859812__note_w2140ab1b5b1b5b3b1b5b3_w2141ab1b5b1b5b3b1b5_w2142ab1b5b1b5b3b1_w2143ab1b5b1b5b3_w2144ab1b5b1b5_w2145ab1b5b1_w2146ab1b5_w2147ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> This is handy for establishing a minimum set of preferences, settings, breakpoints, and watches, that you can use for any debugging session.</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"bei1665702859812__note_w2148ab1b5b1b5b3b3_w2149ab1b5b1b5b3_w2150ab1b5b1b5_w2151ab1b5b1_w2152ab1b5_w2153ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If you have set any watches or breakpoints, these are also saved under that named state.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"bei1665702859812__li_d9185e1_d9186e1_d9187e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Save</span> to save the current settings and preferences.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lbe1677053515050.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuring the Debugger Error and Exception behavior</a><p>The following procedure allows developers to enable or disable Uniface debugger breakpoints based on the defined errors or exceptions break-on conditions on the Settings &gt; Error configuration tab.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fgr1665703523770.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Debugger State</a><p>The state of the Debugger consists of current settings, watches, and breakpoints. The current state can be saved as a named configuration for repeated use.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612084\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612084\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configuring the Uniface Debugger Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configuring the Uniface Debugger You can configure the Uniface Debugger by setting breakpoints and watches, and selecting preferences and settings from the View menu. The Uniface Debugger settings, watches, and breakpoints make up its state, which can be saved to the configuration file for repeated use. Choose View > Settings , click the desired tab, and select the various diagnostic settings you want. Then click Apply . Tab Purpose I/O Print Choose the level of I/O messages that are displayed in the message frame or transcript window. Tracing Choose the level or type of ProcScript-related tracing to be displayed in the message frame or transcript window. Triggers Choose the triggers you want to be enabled or disabled for debugging, or those that you want to be set as breakpoints. Errors Set a specific ProcScript error or exception value ( $procerror ) as a breakpoint. See Configuring the Debugger Error and Exception behavior . Message Frame Specify whether the clrmess ProcScript instruction is enabled or disabled (the default in the Debugger), and display location of application messages. For information on specific settings, click F1 to display the online help. Note: The Triggers and Errors tabs enable you to set general breakpoints. You can also set specific breakpoints in the Debugger main window. See Working with breakpoints . Choose View >Preferences , and select the desired Debugger startup, close, and display preferences. By default, On close: save state & preferences is selected. This ensures that the current state is automatically saved when the Debugger is closed. You can change this, and any other preferences as desired. Optionally, save the current state as a named state. Click Add and provide a name and description for the state. Click the Save to insert a new section with this name and description, containing the current active state, in the configuration file. If you want to update the default state using the current active state, click Update Default . Tip: This is handy for establishing a minimum set of preferences, settings, breakpoints, and watches, that you can use for any debugging session. Note: If you have set any watches or breakpoints, these are also saved under that named state. Click Save to save the current settings and preferences. Related Links Configuring the Debugger Error and Exception behavior The following procedure allows developers to enable or disable Uniface debugger breakpoints based on the defined errors or exceptions break-on conditions on the Settings > Error configuration tab. Debugger State The state of the Debugger consists of current settings, watches, and breakpoints. The current state can be saved as a named configuration for repeated use. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}